  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through various mechanisms and frameworks:\n\n1. Key International Organizations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (UNODC)\n- International Monetary Fund (IMF)\n- World Bank\n\n2. International Legal Frameworks\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group information sharing protocols\n\n3. Mutual Legal Assistance Mechanisms\n- Bilateral and multilateral treaties\n- Extradition agreements\n- Cross-border investigation cooperation\n- Shared intelligence platforms\n\n4. Regulatory Standards\n- Common reporting requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Asset freezing and seizure procedures\n\n5. Implementation Strategies\n- Harmonizing national anti-money laundering (AML) legislation\n- Establishing consistent compliance standards\n- Creating transnational enforcement mechanisms\n\n6. Compliance Enforcement\n- Sanctions for non-compliance\n- International financial system monitoring\n- Reputation-based accountability\n\nThese interconnected approaches help create a comprehensive global strategy against financial crimes.",
